ObAgent: uncertain

The alerts show widespread increases in RPC/span durations (p95/mean) across services — a latency symptom, but that can come from CPU contention, node CPU, or network problems. To disambiguate, run:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric(container.cpu.usage) and whether_is_abnormal_metric(node.cpu.usage) for the affected pods/nodes;
- whether_is_abnormal_metric(container.net.tcp_retransmits) and whether_is_abnormal_metric(container.net.packet_loss) (or tcp.rtt) for those containers;
- collect_trace on an affected call chain to see if time is spent in service processing vs network I/O.
JudgeAgent: No - The history only contains trace symptoms (widespread p95/mean latency rises with different onset minutes — e.g. cartservice-1 at 2022-03-21 22:00:00, frontend-2→currencyservice-0 at 2022-03-21 22:07:00, checkoutservice2-0/paymentservice2-0 at 22:10:00). No single location was established, no anomaly type from the allowed closed set (e.g. node CPU, container network retransmits) was confirmed, no concrete metric/log evidence was given as the root-cause reason, and no single precise start minute was pinned. The agent even marked the hypothesis as uncertain and requested further metric checks. Therefore the root cause is not found.

